## LH-001 Validation — Verdict: CONDITIONAL_PASS

**What the quant-research-agent claimed vs what I found:**

| Metric | Claimed | V2 Independent |
|--------|---------|----------------|
| Pooled p-value | p=0.0067 | p=0.0160 |
| Haley signal | "p≈0.0000 strong" | p=0.1087 (NS) — was a confound |
| Iran signal | "p=0.1829 not significant" | p=0.4818 (NS) ✓ |
| Effect size | r=0.14 (small) | r=0.208 (small-medium) |
| Sample | n=128 candidates | n=59 clean candidates |

**Critical correction:** The v1 "Haley p≈0.0000" finding was a market-scale confound — it compared Haley lifecycle traders against a *mixed* Haley+Iran control. When tested correctly (Haley vs Haley-specific control), the Haley signal is NOT significant (p=0.1087). **Neither event individually validates the heuristic.**

**Key structural finding:** In the Haley market specifically, lifecycle traders (median $724K) made *less* than non-lifecycle Haley traders (median $909K) — the wrong direction for an insider signal.

**Positive finding:** The `insider_signals` table already has 7 real-world detections of exactly this pattern with wallet_age_days as short as 3 days — a stronger signal than the 30-day proxy. Those 7 records are the primary validation path going forward.
